In medium saucepan, cook rice using water and butter according to package directions. Meanwhile, in large skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove bacon from pan, coarsely crumble and set aside. In same large skillet, over medium heat, cook bell pepper, onion and celery in bacon drippings for 6-8 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently. Add cooked rice and beans to vegetable mixture. Stir in bacon. Serve with sour cream.